item.title: Help pleas read
item.dc:creator: @Nets8 Nets8
item.description:
@Nets8 wrote:

0.0.0.0, 127.0.0.1, and localhost are your standard IP addresses. They are the same for everyone and just define your computer, not your local area connection and internet. Your local area connection is the one you use to access your router and can be found in the Control Panel on your start button. Your internet IP address may be found on www.whatismyip.com. This is the IP address that people connect to and people see.
